      • listAsMap

        public static <K,V> Map<K,V> listAsMap(Collection<V> list,
                                       ListUtils.ListKeyToMap<K,V> key)
        Convert a list of object to a map. The key is based on a unique identifier.
        Example: 
        
   ListUtils.ListKeyToMap<Long, Transition> converter = new ListUtils.ListKeyToMap<Long, Transition>() {
       public Long getKey(Transition item) {
           return item.getId(); //Assume an Id exists
       }
   }; Map<Long, Transition> transitionMap =
 ListUtils.listAsMap(transitionList, converter);
        Type Parameters:
        K - The key class
        V - The value class
        Parameters:
        list - The List to convert
        key - ListKeyToMap object
        Returns:
        Map

      • mergeLists

        public static <E extends AbstractEntity> List<E> mergeLists(List<E> oldList,
                                                            List<E> newList)
        This function takes two lists and merge them. This does not preserve any order.
        Assumptions:
        - An element from the new list is new if it has no ID or if it's ID is missing in the old list
        - 2 Abstract entities with the same ID have to be merged
        - An element from the old list has to be removed if its ID is missing in the new list
        Type Parameters:
        E - extends (@see AbstractEntity) the element type
        Parameters:
        oldList - The list containing old elements
        newList - The list containing new elements
        Returns:
        A merged list

      • mergeReplace

        public static <E extends AbstractEntity> List<E> mergeReplace(List<E> oldList,
                                                              List<E> newList)
        This function takes two lists and replace the content of the first one with the content from the second one.
        Merging elements with same id and preserving second list's order.
        Type Parameters:
        E - extends (@see AbstractEntity) the element type
        Parameters:
        oldList - The list containing old elements
        newList - The list containing new elements
        Returns:
        A merged list
